Class Herbivore

java.lang.Object
com.example.projectfx.species.Species
com.example.projectfx.species.Herbivore
All Implemented Interfaces:
Movable, Reproducible, Sleepable
Direct Known Subclasses:
Canari, MarineHerbivore, Rabbit
public abstract class Herbivore extends Species
The Herbivore class represents a herbivorous species in the ecosystem. It includes behaviors for detecting predators, fleeing, and movement. It is an abstract class that serves as a base for specific herbivorous species.

    • hasGroupingInstinct

      public boolean hasGroupingInstinct()
      Returns whether the herbivore has a grouping instinct.
      Returns:
      true if the herbivore prefers to stay in groups, false otherwise.

    • setGroupingInstinct

      public void setGroupingInstinct(boolean groupingInstinct)
      Sets whether the herbivore has a grouping instinct.
      Parameters:
      groupingInstinct - true if the herbivore should prefer to stay in groups, false otherwise.

    • detecterPredateur

      public void detecterPredateur()
      The herbivore detects predators in its vicinity. If a predator is detected, the herbivore will attempt to flee.
